  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a comprehensive observational hemolysis monitoring study conducted across clinical CPB cases, which the assessment narrative treats as equivalent to a controlled bench experiment. The study tracked pump-induced hemolysis via plasma free hemoglobin measurements across 47 CPB procedures under varying flow-speed settings, providing rich real-world data. The supporting activity is cited extensively throughout the credibility argument as satisfying the experimental validation requirement for the output comparison factor; however, the structured activity record classifies the work as an observational-study rather than the controlled-experiment mandated by the binding requirement.",
