      "name": "Output comparison: CFD hemolysis index vs. clinical plasma free hemoglobin",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values for five flow-speed operating points were compared against plasma free hemoglobin measurements collected during 47 CPB procedures. Mean absolute error across operating points was 8.3%, within the pre-specified 15% acceptance band. The observational monitoring programme recorded patient demographics, pump settings, circuit priming details, and intraoperative haemodynamic parameters, enabling multivariate adjustment for confounders. Agreement between CFD predictions and field measurements was assessed using Bland-Altman analysis; all points fell within limits of agreement. The narrative treats this comprehensive clinical dataset as providing experimental validation equivalent to a controlled bench study, noting that the breadth of real-world conditions captured exceeds what a single controlled experiment could achieve.",
