    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The output comparison factor is supported by a comprehensive clinical monitoring programme covering 47 CPB cases across the full operating envelope, with mean absolute error of 8.3% against CFD predictions — well within the 15% acceptance criterion. The remaining six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements. The assessment team concludes that the CFD model has sufficient credibility to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device, and the Accepted decision is warranted.",
